# UBA — Intelligent User Behavior Analytics

> **Context:** The UBA module is currently a near-empty stub (91-line engine, no DB models, no real API). The system already has a mature [AnomalyDetector](file:///M:/%D9%86%D8%B3%D8%AE%20%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B9/enterprise_ngfw/modules/ids_ips/engine/anomaly_detector.py#48-243) in IDS/IPS with Isolation Forest, ONNX, and sklearn support. Industry research confirms that 2024-grade UEBA requires behavioral baselines + dynamic risk scoring + multi-source correlation.

---

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Network Events / Auth Logs] --> B[UBAEventCollector]
    B --> C[UserProfiler - Baseline Engine]
    C --> D{Analysis Layer}
    D --> E[TimeAnomalyAnalyzer]
    D --> F[LocationAnomalyAnalyzer]
    D --> G[DataExfilDetector]
    D --> H[PrivilegeEscalationDetector]
    D --> I[PeerGroupComparator]
    E & F & G & H & I --> J[RiskScoreAggregator]
    J --> K[(DB: uba_user_profiles)]
    J --> L[(DB: uba_events)]
    J --> M[API / Alerts]
```

## 1 — Database Layer ([system/database/database.py](file:///M:/%D9%86%D8%B3%D8%AE%20%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B9/enterprise_ngfw/system/database/database.py))

Three new SQLAlchemy models:

| Model | Table | Purpose |
|-------|-------|---------|
| `UBAUserProfile` | `uba_user_profiles` | Per-user behavioral baseline (rolling stats) |
| `UBAEvent` | `uba_events` | Individual behavior events with anomaly score |
| `UBAConfig` | `uba_config` | Settings (thresholds, enable/disable detectors) |

### `UBAUserProfile` fields
- `username`, `user_id` → FK to [users](file:///M:/%D9%86%D8%B3%D8%AE%20%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B9/enterprise_ngfw/system/database/database.py#207-226)
- `typical_hours_start/end` — learned work hours (int)
- `known_ips` (JSON list, up to 30)
- `known_services` (JSON list, up to 100)
- `avg_daily_bytes`, `max_daily_bytes`, `daily_bytes_stddev`
- `avg_failed_logins`, `avg_session_duration`
- `peer_group` — department/role label for comparison
- `risk_score` — current running risk (0–100)
- `risk_level` — `low|medium|high|critical`
- `last_seen`, `created_at`, `updated_at`
- `event_count` — total events analyzed
- `baseline_locked` — bool; locked = enough data to trust baseline

### `UBAEvent` fields
- `username`, `source_ip`, `target_service`
- `bytes_transferred`, `session_duration`
- `event_time` — actual event timestamp
- `anomaly_score` (0.0–1.0), `risk_contribution`
- `detectors_triggered` (JSON list of detector names)
- `action_taken` — `allow|alert|block`
- `details` (JSON)

### `UBAConfig` fields
- [enabled](file:///M:/%D9%86%D8%B3%D8%AE%20%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B9/enterprise_ngfw/modules/email_security/engine/core/settings.py#182-185), [mode](file:///M:/%D9%86%D8%B3%D8%AE%20%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B9/enterprise_ngfw/modules/email_security/engine/core/settings.py#186-191) — `monitor|enforce|learning`
- `baseline_min_events` — events before baseline is trusted (default 50)
- `max_known_ips`, `max_known_services`
- `thresholds` (JSON) — per-detector thresholds
- `alert_on_risk_level` — trigger alert above this level

---

## 2 — Engine (`modules/uba/engine/`)

### `engine/core/user_profiler.py` ← **[REWRITE]** of `user_behavior.py`
The central brain. Replaces the old 91-line file:
- `UserProfiler` class that:
  - Loads/saves `UBAUserProfile` from DB (not in-memory only)
  - Updates rolling stats using **exponential moving average (EMA)** — so the baseline adapts over time without being hijacked by a single burst
  - Manages a **baseline locking** mechanism: once N events seen, baseline is "trusted"
  - Exposes `analyze(event: UBAEvent) -> float` that runs all detectors

### `engine/detectors/time_detector.py` ← **[NEW]**
- Detects off-hours access
- Uses a **3-sigma rule**: if event hour is > 3σ from the user's typical hour distribution, flag it
- Score: 0.0–0.35

### `engine/detectors/location_detector.py` ← **[NEW]**
- Detects unknown IPs (new location)
- Bonus: if IP is in a **new country** vs. last known IPs (using IP-prefix heuristics), escalate score
- Score: 0.0–0.45

### `engine/detectors/exfil_detector.py` ← **[NEW]**
- Tracks `bytes_transferred` against user's `avg_daily_bytes + 2*stddev`
- Large upload to unknown destination = high score
- Score: 0.0–0.40

### `engine/detectors/privilege_detector.py` ← **[NEW]**
- Tracks access to services far outside `known_services`
- If high-privilege service (VPN, admin panels, SSH) accessed for first time: high score
- Score: 0.0–0.35

### `engine/detectors/peer_detector.py` ← **[NEW]**
- If the user's behavior deviates strongly from their **peer group** (same role/department), flag it
- Uses simple z-score against peer group averages stored in profiles

### `engine/core/risk_aggregator.py` ← **[NEW]**
- Takes scores from all detectors
- Computes **weighted sum** (weights stored in `UBAConfig.thresholds`)
- Maps to: `low (0–25) | medium (25–55) | high (55–80) | critical (80–100)`
- Updates the user's running `risk_score` with EMA so one event doesn't spike or clear the score

### `engine/core/uba_plugin.py` ← **[NEW]** (InspectorPlugin)
- Extends `InspectorPlugin` from `system.inspection_core.framework.plugin_base`
- `can_inspect()` → returns True for TCP/Auth traffic on known ports
- `inspect()` → extracts user identity from context metadata → calls `UserProfiler.analyze()` → returns `InspectionResult`

### `engine/__init__.py` ← **[MODIFY]**
- Export `UBAPlugin` for ModuleManager

